These last two logs are interesting, `{:type "transfer-success", :action 4}}` means that the pairing process should be complete. However `Initiated local pairing` is called after

```
09-13 12:14:28.943 11089 11421 I ReactNativeJS: INFO [status-im.signals.core:33] - local pairing signal received {:event {:type "transfer-success", :action 4}}
09-13 12:14:28.946 11089 11421 I ReactNativeJS: INFO [status-im2.contexts.syncing.events:70] - Initiated local pairing {:response "{\"error\":\"\"}", :event :syncing/input-connection-string-for-bootstrapping}
```

After successful pairing, It seems like the node is stopped which gives back the error `JSON-RPC client is unavailable` for login events (the mobile automatically logs in the newly paired user). This gives an impression to the user that the syncing in progress screen is struck.

Below is the log from latest `develop` running on iOS simulator:

```log
 INFO  INFO [status-im.signals.core:33] - local pairing signal received {:event {:type "process-success", :action 3}}
 INFO  INFO [status-im.signals.core:33] - local pairing signal received {:event {:type "transfer-success", :action 4}}
 INFO  INFO [status-im2.contexts.syncing.events:70] - Initiated local pairing {:response "{\"error\":\"\"}", :event :syncing/input-connection-string-for-bootstrapping}
 ERROR  ERROR [status-im2.contexts.shell.activity-center.events:496] - Failed to fetch count of notifications {:error "JSON-RPC client is unavailable"}
 WARN  WARN [status-im2.contexts.shell.activity-center.events:427] - Failed to load Activity Center notifications 5
 WARN  WARN [status-im2.contexts.shell.activity-center.events:427] - Failed to load Activity Center notifications 5
